Detectives from the Special Crimes Unit have recovered an extra Sh2 million of the money stolen from Standard Chartered Bank and G4S in Langâ€™ata, Nairobi, earlier in September. The money was found in Machakos County over the weekend following a tip-off that led to the arrest of three suspects. According to police reports, the detectives arrested one John Kamau Mulei who led them to the house of his grandmother Mary Kyalo at Kalumoni village in Machakos. They found Sh2,389,000 at the house. CHARGES The report indicated that the suspect is the brother of one Bernard Mwendwa who was arrested last week in connection to the robbery. Nairobi region police boss Philip Ndolo told the Nation that the Directorate of Criminal Investigations will process the three for arraignment. The finding brings to Sh9 million the total amount of money recovered following the theft of Sh72 million. Some of the money was stolen while being transported from the G4S headquarters along Witu Road and the rest from Standard Chartered's ATM in Nairobi West.  